Job Description:
The Human Resource Manager is a leader in promoting CPCS’s values and oversees CPCS recruitment, performance management, staff compensation and benefits, and compliance to Cambodia’s Labor statutes.

The Human Resource Manager is responsible for maintaining and enhancing the organization’s human resource by ensuring staff’s work and life balance, generate a conducive and productive workplace by creating the community feeling in CPCS where all staff know their rights and responsibilities and each staff has way to express their concerns. The Human Resource Manager is involved in all legal compliance and administration of human resource requirements.

** Expected Duties and Responsibilities
•	Ensure CPCS has clear and up to date HR policies and procedures that are compliant to Cambodia’s employment requirement, well implemented and supportive to CPCS core values and over all mission;

•	Lead in recruitment processes with hiring directors/managers following CPCS hiring procedures and in new hire induction and onboarding;

•	Cover all areas of compliance with Cambodia’s employment laws and requirement such as foreigner work permit, Khmer work employment book, staff turn-over, etc.;

•	Prepare employment contract, consultancy contract and internship contract;

•	Research, analyse and propose compensation and benefit pay packages;

•	Maintain knowledge of trends, best practices, regulatory changes and new technologies in human resources, staff management and employment law;

•	Create and initiate learning and development programs for staff development;

•	Oversee employee’s disciplinary meetings, investigations and terminations;

•	Organize and maintain personnel records;

•	Keep record of staff on travel including destination country, address of accommodation and contact details;

•	Ensure all staff are registered and covered by insurance;

•	Update CPCS organization chart;

•	Process and administer ACTS students’ accidental insurance during in-person modules;

•	Provide timely support to all CPCS staff on all possible human resource concern;

•	Promotion of staff well-being in the work place by creating a work friendly environment;

•	Perform other duties as determined by the CPCS Executive Director and/or CPCS Co-directors

This position is full time, based in Siem Reap, Cambodia. Preference will be given to Cambodian candidates. Compensation package includes salary (less Cambodia income withholding taxes), savings and pension contributions, health insurance, working documents. Salary is commensurate with experience.

Providing seamless support to the BOD including but not limited to: diary management, arranging meetings and calls, report and document preparation, preparing detailed international travel, making bookings and generally being proactive to ensure the BOD is well prepared for all meetings and visit on a day-to-day basis.

** Duties and Responsibilities:
•	Facilitate the organization of meetings by scheduling the meeting, inviting participants, ordering refreshments, booking equipment and meeting rooms, preparing and distributing agendas and taking minutes, and greeting visitors so that meetings are efficiently and effectively organized;
•	Ensure meetings are both regular, which can be scheduled well in advance, responding to urgent requests for support;
•	Ensure the meetings are organized efficiently and to the satisfaction of the BOD;
•	Support to the BOD in preparation for board committee meetings and other formal meetings;
•	Organize and facilitate guests according to the instructions of BOD;
•	Manage smoothest flow of document submission for approval;
•	Arrange and attend meeting, Company visit, Lunch and Dinner with guest as required;
•	Manage travels of the boss such as air ticket, hotel booking, car rental, budget planning, trip schedule, expenses clearing and documents preparation;
•	Manage company and personal confidential data (soft and hard copies);
•	Check the monthly payroll for employees;
•	Deliver messages from Top management down to all related persons and ensure for the returned quick response.
•	Perform other tasks as required.

Job Requirement:
•	A bachelor degree with a major in business or Admin;
•	At least 3 years of relevant secretarial experience to Top management companies;
•	Good communication skills and the ability to work with people are essential;
•	Strong planning skills, leader ship skills and pay attention to details;
•	Great negotiator, good interpersonal skills, caring and a good listener; 
•	Fluent spoken and written English and able to conduct presentation with high confidence.

Job Description:
About The Job:

As a compliance officer assist Senior Associate, AML-CFT Compliance in ensuring that CMCB establishes and maintains an effective, best practices compliance and integrity program to prevent, detect and report compliance issues to promote ethical practices and ensure the faithful implementation of the program as directed by the line manager. 

What You Will Do:

•	Assist to ensure compliance with current AML regulations and other relevant legislation;
•	Assist in conducting AML/CFT risk assessment for products and services, customers, and other issues relating to AML/CFT;
•	Perform transaction monitoring on non-cash and cash transactions to detect and report suspicious activities/transactions;
•	Maintain records of ECDD on high-risk customers, and suspicious activities/transactions.
•	Assist in analyzing new and pending laws which will affect the Bank's current operations, develops and periodically reviews and updates the policies and procedures to ensure compliance with the applicable laws and regulations. Participate in compliance assurance with NBC Prakas and other laws and regulations
•	Assist in compliance assurance with NBC Prakas and other laws and regulations across the bank-wide;
•	Perform compliance checks on AML/CFT requirements in line with the bank policies and procedures;
•	Perform CDD and ECDD checks on counterparties, business partners, and intermediaries where appropriate;
•	Assist in issuing AML/CFT guidelines, processes, and procedures;
•	Prepares and presents periodic reports to the supervisor concerning the Bank's current record of compliance.
•	Performs other job-related duties as assigned by the line manager.

About The Job:

As an officer, Regulatory Compliance will work under the leadership of an Associate, Regulatory Compliance is to ensure effective administration of the CMBC’s compliance program with a particular focus on regulatory compliance; specifically, this position will focus on assisting in the development, administration, monitoring, evaluating and testing of the regulatory compliance program in all areas were relevant to the banking industry.

What You Will Do:

•	Assist in developing and administrating the regulatory compliance program in all areas relevant to the banking industry;
•	Advise on the relevant regulatory requirements to respective business and support departments
•	Assist in monitoring, testing, and evaluating the regulatory compliance program to ensure its effectiveness and permanent compliance;
•	Obtain and understand regulatory updates from relevant authorities, validate their applicability to different units, and ensure timely dissemination to the concerned;
•	Perform gap analysis on all applicable regulatory issuances, define actions to be taken and the timeline for compliance;
•	Coordinate with business units in the preparation of the accurate and timely submission of all regulatory reports;
•	Assist to review and advise on all CMCB’s frameworks, policies, and procedures to ensure that all regulatory requirements are incorporated;
•	Maintain compliance awareness by conducting periodic training for all respective employees on related regulatory requirements.

